/*----------------------------------------------------------------------------+
 |                                                                            |
 |                                INSTALL                                     |
 |                                                                            |
 +----------------------------------------------------------------------------*/

 Note:
 -------
 To run and use domus.Link you must first install Heyu. For more information
 please refer to http://heyu.org
 
 
 Assumptions:
 --------------
 The following install procedures assumes the following:
 
 - Heyu configuration files located in /etc/heyu
 - Websever root folder is /var/www
 - And domus.Link is being installed in /var/www/domus.Link
 
 
 Installation:
 --------------

 1) Download latest version from http://domus.link.co.pt/download

 2) Un-tar to a location within the webserver root or a specific directory.
 
    ie: 
        mv domuslink-XXX.tar.gz /var/www
        cd /var/www
        tar xfvz domuslink-XXX.tar.gz

 3) Backup existing x10.conf file (VERY IMPORTANT)

    ie:
        cp /etc/heyu/x10.conf /etc/heyu/x10.conf.backup

 4) Copy supplied x10.conf to heyu conf. directory (VERY IMPORTANT)
    
    ie: 
        cp /var/www/domus.Link/x10.conf /etc/heyu/x10.conf
        
    The supplied x10.conf file is prepared for use with the frontend and 
    therefore must be used. The x10.conf file supplied with Heyu will not 
    work with domus.Link.

 5) Edit x10.conf file and change TTY directive to suit your system.
    - Do not add tabs, or extra spaces between options and directives.
    - Do not add comments, or any other text.
    - Leave everything else as is.
    
    ie:
        vi /etc/heyu/x10.conf

 6) Change file permission so that webserver can read/write to the following files:
    - /etc/heyu/x10.conf
    - /var/www/domus.Link/db/floorplan 
    - /var/www/domus.Link/config.php
    
    ie: 
        chown apache:apache /etc/heyu/x10.conf /var/www/domus.Link/db/floorplan /var/www/domus.Link/config.php
    
    or: 
        chmod o+rw /etc/heyu/x10.conf /var/www/domus.Link/db/floorplan /var/www/domus.Link/config.php

 7) Setup apache acordingly, refer to http://httpd.apache.org if you don't know
    how to do this.
    
 8) Finally, point your web browser to you webserver. 
    If you placed it in the root folder /var/www/ http://localhost should suffice.
    If you placed it in /var/www/domus.Link then http://localhost/domus.Link


 ------------------------------------------------------------------------
 The next step might not be required, however, if you keep getting a
 "HEYU: Can't open TTY line. check permissions!" then please follow it.
 ------------------------------------------------------------------------


 X) Change permission on TTY port so that heyu can use it.
    
    The typically used port is /dev/ttyS0 which usually is a sym. link to
    /dev/tts/0 so in this case use the following commands:
    
    ie: chmod o+rw /dev/ttyS0
    or: chmod o+rw /dev/tts/0
    
    To check where /dev/ttyS0 links to, issue the following command:
    
    ls -l /dev/ttyS0
    
 